cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.RO, cs.SY 

This paper presents a novel modular architecture for StarCraft II AI that utilizes deep reinforcement learning techniques to train two of its modules. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves optimization and decision-making, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.GT (Game Theory). Additionally, the use of a centralized scheduler and updater implies that it could be relevant to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
